Citi Joins U.K. N2EX Exchange; Spot Trade Starts April

-- B y   C a t h e r i n e   A i r l i e
-- 
2011-02-14T11:03:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-14/citigroup-joins-n2ex-power-exchange-run-by-nasdaq-omx-nord-pool-spot.html
  Citigroup Inc .’s global markets unit
 joined N2EX , a U.K. power exchange operated by  Nasdaq OMX Group
Inc . and Nord Pool Spot AS, and spot trade is scheduled to begin
April 4.  N2EX started a day-ahead auction of U.K. power contracts in
January 2010 and trades physical deals as much as a month into
the future. A derivatives market started Jan. 31 and requires
separate membership. The exchange will start handling same-day
U.K. electricity contracts on April 4, according to a  statement 
on the bourse’s website.  Newedge Group’s British unit joined the exchange as a
clearing member for U.K. power derivative contracts. EDF SA,
E.ON AG and  UBS AG  are the three named members that have signed
up to trade the futures contracts. There is one unidentified
member of the futures market  To contact the reporter on this story:
Catherine Airlie in London at 
